  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Jamieson-Fausset-Brown Bible Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "3. one said—literally, \"he said to himself,\"",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Is not this Bath-sheba? &c.—She seems to have been a celebrated beauty, whose renown had already reached the ears of David, as happens in the East, from reports carried by the women from harem to harem.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Bath-sheba, the daughter of Eliam—or Ammiel (1Ch 3:5), one of David's worthies (2Sa 23:34), and son of Ahithophel.",
        "children": []
      }
    ]
  },
