        "text": "David ordered inquiry to be made about her, and found (ויּאמר, \"he, i.e., the messenger, said;\" or indefinitely, \"they said\") that she was Bathsheba, the wife of Uriah the Hethite. הלוא, nonne, is used, as it frequently is, in the sense of an affirmation, \"it is indeed so.\" Instead of Bathsheba the daughter of Eliam, we find the name given in the Chronicles (",
